n header on the cargo/vault grid; the default arm IS the retail server's documented response to unknown TargetInv (the LogMessage call is the retail diagnostic). Zero permissiveness added; not loosening any security posture; not fabricating any reply (the default arm emits none). Reinforces the seam-discovery catalogue with a NEW variant: \"server-only LogMessage default arm with no client-observable reply\" — distinct from the SendVaMessage UNRECOGNISED-error pattern used by Waves 24/26/27 because the inventory-sort default arm doesn't even bother with a user-facing message (the retail UI assumes the user only ever clicks valid TargetInv column headers, so a bad value is treated as developer-only diagnostic rather than user-facing error)."),
