ct {int32_t UIChange; int32_t UIType} (common/include/net7/PacketStructures.h:534-538) from the two arguments and emits via SendOpcode(ENB_OPCODE_0066_OPEN_INTERFACE, &set_interface, sizeof(set_interface)=8). For UIChange=0, UIType=0 the wire payload is exactly 8 bytes of zeros. Reply is a back-to-self 0x0066 frame; the test also receives a 0x001D MESSAGE_STRING from SendVaMessage but doesn't assert on it (0x001D is already covered by Wave 19). Test asserts payload.Length==8, bytes[0..4]==0 (UIChange echo), bytes[4..8]==0 (UIType echo). Catches: (a) 0x0066 emit removal at PlayerConnection.cpp:3583 — drain times out; (b) SetInterface wire-layout regression at PacketStructures.h:534-538 — currently 8B packed {int32_t UIChange; int32_t UIType}; widening either field to `long` on Linux x86_64 grows to 12B/16B respectively and the length assertion catches; (c) Player::OpenInterface signature regression — the function takes `long UIChange, long UIType` at PlayerConnection.cpp:3576 but the SetInterface fields are int32_t at line 537, so the implicit narrowing at the assignment is a one-way truncation; a refactor swapping the assignment direction or widening the struct fields would surface; (d) single-slash gate regression at PlayerConnection.cpp:5447 — if a refactor tightens the gate (e.g. requires double-slash, adds AdminLevel check, rejects Msg[1]='o') the openif arm never fires; (e) case 'o' dispatch regression in the single-slash switch (PlayerConnection.cpp:6885) — if the switch label gets moved/removed or an earlier MatchOptWithParam in case 'o' eats the \"openif\" prefix (e.g. matching \"open\" via allowNoParams) the openif arm never runs; (f) MatchOptWithParam parsing regression at PlayerConnection.cpp:4526-4554 — splits on `=` or ` `; a refactor narrowing the separator set (e.g. `=`-only) would stop parsing \"openif 0,0\" — drain times out; (g) strtok_s second-call regression at PlayerConnection.cpp:6887-6888 — if `b` comes back NULL the `if (b)` guard skips the O