e inner-opcode guard at UDPProxyToClient_linux.cpp:568 tightening — currently passes 0x0034 CLIENT_SET_TIME and 0x001B AUX_DATA because both < 0x0FFF. Per CLAUDE.md server-integrity: 0x0079 with Terminal=0 is what retail Win32 client emits when the user closes a manufacture terminal in a starbase; the all-break inner switch + SetDifficulty(0) + ResetManuItems + SendAuxManu is exactly what the retail server does to reset session state for the next terminal entry. Zero permissiveness added; not loosening any security posture; not fabricating any reply. Earlier wave triage that bulk-flagged the manufacture-action family (0x0079/0x007A/0x007B/0x007C/0x007E) as UNSAFE was overly pessimistic — only the Terminal=1/2/4 mode-set arms actually mutate ManuIndex state; the Terminal=0 exit arm is fully fresh-char-safe."),
